  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">AHM has begun to implement specialized pilot programs in early 2015 to empower women and youth of P&#xE1;tzcuaro lake basin. With additional funding, AHM seeks to build on its programming with these vulnerable populations and expand its mental health services through intensive trainings, community capacity building, leadership and empowerment strategies, and specialized mental health programming based on Heartland Alliance International&#x2019;s (HAI) trauma-informed care model. 
The goals of this project are to:
-provide better access to psychosocial services and increased community supportive systems to promote social change
-help youth take a positive role and become agents of change in their communities
-women have better access to conditions to build a future for themselves and their families</narrative>
  </description>
